<subSubSection id="67B04BF80D30A402FF68FA813BBF006B" pageId="1" pageNumber="159" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="2F1518730D30A402FF68FA813E4D034E" blockId="1.[189,310,1344,1370]" box="[189,310,1344,1370]" pageId="1" pageNumber="159">
<heading id="745DAF1F0D30A402FF68FA813E4D034E" bold="true" box="[189,310,1344,1370]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="159" reason="3">
<emphasis id="1DDEC4610D30A402FF68FA813E4D034E" bold="true" box="[189,310,1344,1370]" pageId="1" pageNumber="159">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2F1518730D30A402FF68FAAE3BBF006B" blockId="1.[189,1401,1391,1664]" pageId="1" pageNumber="159">
The species is distinguished from many of the Oriental and Palearctic species by the absence of modified tergites on segment VI–VIII. It resembles the Bornean 
<taxonomicName id="E8AA63F00D30A402FCBAFA533BA003B9" authority="Malicky, 2005" authorityName="Malicky" authorityYear="2005" box="[879,1243,1426,1453]" class="Insecta" family="Leptoceridae" genus="Oecetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peleus">
<emphasis id="1DDEC4610D30A402FCBAFA533B6403B8" box="[879,1055,1426,1452]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="159">Oecetis peleus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="4B3B65820D30A402FBFEFA533BA003B9" author="Malicky H." box="[1067,1243,1426,1453]" pageId="1" pageNumber="159" pagination="605 - 669" refId="ref2697" refString="Malicky H. 2005. Beitrage zur Kenntnis asiatischer Oecetis (Trichoptera, Leptoceridae). Linzer biologische Beitrage 27: 605 - 669." type="journal article" year="2005">Malicky, 2005</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E8AA63F00D30A402FACBFA533D7903C4" authority="Malicky, 2005" authorityName="Malicky" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Leptoceridae" genus="Oecetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="halirrhotios">
<emphasis id="1DDEC4610D30A402FACBFA533E3203DB" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="159">Oecetis halirrhotios</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="4B3B65820D30A402FE81FA743D7903C4" author="Malicky H." box="[340,514,1461,1488]" pageId="1" pageNumber="159" pagination="605 - 669" refId="ref2697" refString="Malicky H. 2005. Beitrage zur Kenntnis asiatischer Oecetis (Trichoptera, Leptoceridae). Linzer biologische Beitrage 27: 605 - 669." type="journal article" year="2005">
Malicky, 
<quantity id="E852B5960D30A402FE12FA743D7903C4" box="[455,514,1461,1488]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0927" pageId="1" pageNumber="159" unit="in" value="2005.0">2005</quantity>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
in genitalic features, particularly in the shape of tergum X, the inferior appendages of the inferior appendages and the superior appendages. However, it is distinguished from both species by the presence of a row of short megasetae forming a comb along the mesal margin of the inferior appendages and by the phallus bearing a pair of sharply triangular lateral processes on the posterior part of the ventral side compared to rounded processes in 
<taxonomicName id="E8AA63F00D30A402FC0AF9833B360048" authorityName="Malicky" authorityYear="2005" box="[991,1101,1602,1628]" class="Insecta" family="Leptoceridae" genus="Oecetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peleus">
<emphasis id="1DDEC4610D30A402FC0AF9833B360048" box="[991,1101,1602,1628]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="159">O. peleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E8AA63F00D30A402FB5CF9833A420048" authorityName="Malicky" authorityYear="2005" box="[1161,1337,1602,1628]" class="Insecta" family="Leptoceridae" genus="Oecetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="halirrhotios">
<emphasis id="1DDEC4610D30A402FB5CF9833A420048" box="[1161,1337,1602,1628]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="159">O. halirrhotios</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is also distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="E8AA63F00D30A402FE0DF9A43D3C006B" authorityName="Malicky" authorityYear="2005" box="[472,583,1637,1663]" class="Insecta" family="Leptoceridae" genus="Oecetis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="159" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peleus">
<emphasis id="1DDEC4610D30A402FE0DF9A43D3C006B" box="[472,583,1637,1663]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="159">O. peleus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the more strongly curved tergum X in lateral view.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="67B04BF80D30A402FF68F9663A3600FB" box="[189,1357,1703,1776]" pageId="1" pageNumber="159" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="2F1518730D30A402FF68F9663E3F00D5" blockId="1.[189,324,1703,1729]" box="[189,324,1703,1729]" pageId="1" pageNumber="159">
<heading id="745DAF1F0D30A402FF68F9663E3F00D5" bold="true" box="[189,324,1703,1729]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="1" pageNumber="159" reason="3">
<emphasis id="1DDEC4610D30A402FF68F9663E3F00D5" bold="true" box="[189,324,1703,1729]" pageId="1" pageNumber="159">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2F1518730D30A402FF68F9173A3600FB" blockId="1.[189,1357,1749,1776]" box="[189,1357,1749,1776]" pageId="1" pageNumber="159">
<emphasis id="1DDEC4610D30A402FF68F9173E4700FB" box="[189,316,1750,1775]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="159">Mesospina</emphasis>
, referring to the row of spine-like megasetae along the mesal margin of the coxopodites.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
